The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in England so far as at 25 October is 740,262 (1,315.2 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 20 October, there were 113,205 new confirmed cases (201.1 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 13 October, there were 94,784 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 19% (18,421 extra cases).
